NYT of May 25, 1915
  <a href="http://query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=940DE2DB1338E633A25756C2A9639C946496D6CF" rel="nofollow">query.nytimes.com/gst/abstract.html?res=940DE2DB1338E633A...</a>
reported &quot;NEWPORT, R.I., May 24. -- Through the assistance given by Captain Roger Welles, commanding officer of the Naval Training Station, a public welcome will be held tomorrow noon on the return to the station of the historic corvette Constellation from Norfolk. Mayor Robert S. Burlingame will preside, and Captain Welles will read a history of the ship. &quot;
